# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.railway.example — Railway deployment (OpenRouter API)
# Model server: OpenRouter API (no GPU, no Ollama)
# Agent server: Docker container on Railway (free/hobby tier)
#
# ⚠ Do NOT commit a .env file with your OpenRouter key to git.
#   Set all variables in the Railway dashboard instead (see below).
#   This file is reference only — never copy it to .env with real secrets.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Set ALL of these in Railway dashboard → Project → Service → Variables ─────

MODEL_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
MODEL_NAME=qwen/qwen3-8b
MODEL_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx          # ← your OpenRouter secret key

COST_PER_INPUT_TOKEN=0.00000005                      # $0.05 / M input tokens
COST_PER_OUTPUT_TOKEN=0.0000004                      # $0.40 / M output tokens

# OpenRouter uses these to identify your app in their dashboard,
# apply per-app rate limits, and display usage attribution.
OPENROUTER_REFERER=https://your-portfolio.vercel.app # ← replace with your Vercel URL
OPENROUTER_TITLE=Portfolio Infrastructure Demo       # ← display name in OpenRouter dashboard

MAX_CONCURRENT_RUNS=3

# ── What to set where (outside this file) ────────────────────────────────────
#
# RAILWAY DASHBOARD (railway.app → Project → Service → Variables):
#   Set every variable above here.  Railway injects them into the container.
#
# OPENROUTER (openrouter.ai → Keys):
#   Create a new key → copy the sk-or-v1-... value → paste into MODEL_API_KEY
#   in Railway dashboard.
#
#   Rate limits (free tier): ~60 requests/minute, ~200 requests/day
#   To raise limits: openrouter.ai → API Keys → Edit → Rate limit
#   The server caps at MAX_CONCURRENT_RUNS=3 so demo traffic stays within free tier.
#
# VERCEL (portfolio-frontend repo):
#   NUXT_OPENROUTER_AGENT_URL = the Railway app URL (shown in Railway dashboard)
#                               e.g. https://agent-server-production.up.railway.app
#
# GITHUB ACTIONS SECRETS (this repo → Settings → Secrets):
#   VAST_API_KEY     — needed for automated Vast.ai start/stop (unrelated to Railway)
#   VAST_INSTANCE_ID — same as above

# ── How Railway deploys this ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Railway detects the Dockerfile in this repo and builds a container image.
# Start command (from Dockerfile CMD):
#   langgraph dev --port $PORT --host 0.0.0.0 --no-browser --max-concurrent-runs 3
# Railway sets $PORT automatically — no configuration needed.
